<p>Where should form action be defined when using jQuery Validate plugin?</p>  <p>In the JavaScript?</p>  <p>Or in the form?</p>  <p>Or both?</p>  <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; &lt;html&gt;     &lt;head&gt;         &lt;meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8"&gt;         &lt;title&gt;Testing&lt;/title&gt;         //Links to script go here...           &lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;              $(function(){                 var validator=$("#myForm").validate({                     rules: {},                     messages: {},                     submitHandler: function(form) {                         $.post('some/url/to/post/to.php',$(form).serializeArray(),function (json){                         //Or maybe use form.action as url?  Gives full URL: http://subdomain.example.com/some/url/to/post/to.php                         //Or maybe use $(form).attr('action') as url?  Gives partial URL: some/url/to/post/to.php                             //bla bla bla                             },'json');                      }                 });                             });         &lt;/script&gt;     &lt;/head&gt;      &lt;body&gt;         &lt;form id="myForm" action="some/url/to/post/to.php" method="post"&gt;             &lt;input type="text" name="bla"&gt;             &lt;input type="submit" value="sumbit"&gt;         &lt;/form&gt;     &lt;/body&gt;  &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>